Subject: 24th General Assembly of Nova Scotia 
To: Tom
Content:
The 24th General Assembly of Nova Scotia represented Nova Scotia between 1867 and 1871. John J. Marshall was chosen as speaker for the house. Jared C. Troop was named speaker in February 1870 after Marshall's death. The assembly was dissolved on April 17, 1871. W.H. Wylde (1870) Philip Carteret Hill (1870) Conservative Hugh McDonald (1868) Liberal Notes:
